          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, non-fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Biogene carbon content of maize grain on a dry matter basis 47.886%
 Carbon content of biomass fractions from Rouwenhorst et al (1991) (carbohydrates and proteins) and  Nemecek and Kägi 2007 (lipids, fibres ash). Carbohydrate, protein, lipid and fibre contents of from Feedipedia.
Sources:Heuzé V., Tran G., Lebas F. (2017) Maize grain. Feedipedia, a programme by INRAE, CIRAD, AFZ and FAO. https://www.feedipedia.org/node/556 Last updated on September 7, 2017, 14:29. 
Rouwenhorst, Frank Jzn, Scheffers &amp; van Dijken  (1991) Determination of protein concentration by total organic carbon analysis. Journal of Biochemical and Biophysical Methods, 22:119–128.https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/0165022X9190024Q
Nemecek T. &amp; Kägi T. (2007) Life Cycle Inventories of Swiss and European Agricultural Production Systems. Final report ecoinvent V2.0 No. 15a. Agroscope Reckenholz-Taenikon Research Station ART, Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Zurich and Dübendorf, Switzerland, retrieved from: www.ecoinvent.ch.</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="3a0af1d6-04c3-41c6-a3da-92c4f61e0eaa" amount="0.805724243630299" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">dry mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="6bc8ac5e-cc4c-45fb-93dc-53c0e45091df" amount="15.0670433558866" unitId="980b811e-3905-4797-82a5-173f5568bc7e">
          <name xml:lang="en">energy content</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The gross energy content of maize grain is 18.7MJ/kg on a dry matter basis, 87.2% dry matter as fed for North American maize grain (Feedipedia - Maize 2017). At the harvest moisture content of 19.4% (2014-2021, USDA NASS 2021a), the energy content of maize grain is 15.1MJ/kg product weight.
Source(s): 
Heuzé V., Tran G., Lebas F. (2017) Maize grain. Feedipedia, a programme by INRAE, CIRAD, AFZ and FAO. https://www.feedipedia.org/node/556 Last updated on September 7, 2017, 14:29. 
USDA NASS (2021a) CORN, AT HARVEST, GRAIN - MOISTURE, 5 YEAR AVG, MEASURED IN PCT. US Department of Agriculture (USDA). https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/13FC0C89-E211-3D0B-A9C5-BCFC35728512)</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.114322116" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The price per kg of maize grain is considering for the years 2014-2021 for the state of Iowa in the US. The values were retrieved in $/BU [1] and converted into $/kg considering a conversion factor of 1/25.4 [2]. References: [1] US Department of Agriculture (NASS), Quickstat, TabLe "CORN, GRAIN - PRICE RECEIVED, MEASURED IN $ / BU", accessed on 25.08.2023, available at: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/ [2] https://www.rayglen.com/grain-conversion-calculator/
The prices were converted to EUR based on the annual exchange rates published by the European Central Bank (https://sdw.ecb.europa.eu/quickview.do?SERIES_KEY=120.EXR.A.AUD.EUR.SP00.A, last accessed on 2023-06-01) and adjusted for inflation relative to 2005 using the producer price index (PPI) of the euro area, published by eurostat (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/STS_INPP_A__custom_6416181/default/table?lang=en, last accessed on 2023-06-01).</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="a9358458-9724-4f03-b622-106eda248916" amount="0.241119412634731" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
