      <intermediateExchange id="e99b7346-5686-5933-88d9-4e76cb3b963b" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="000095-73-8" amount="1.0166206218491E-05" intermediateExchangeId="04ec6467-1e9f-426c-b84a-687d6164b6c1" activityLinkId="a13caffa-fe39-5f56-88ea-9f208093389f">
        <name xml:lang="en">2,4-dichlorotoluene</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">1.04E-2 MJ/kg diesel, burned in agricultural machinery 
Based on agricultural extension expert estimates of annual costs for haulage - moving grain from field to storage - and general fuel use (enterprise crop budgets including IA, NE, IL) and farmer survey data (Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (ISU), Wisconsin Farm Custom Rate Survey 2021 (USDA, NASS, Wisconsin Field Office)).
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance. Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. 
Sources:
ISU Extension 2021a; UNL Extension 2020; Langemeier MR, Nielsen B, Vyn TJ, Casteel S, and Johnson B 2021; Plastina, Johanns, Gleisner, Qualman 2021; WI NASS 2021
Langemeier MR, Nielsen B, Vyn TJ, Casteel S, and Johnson B (2021) 2022 Purdue Crop Cost &amp; Return Guide. Purdue Extension Publ. ID-166-W. Purdue Extension - University of Indiana. https://ag.purdue.edu/commercialag/home/resource/2021/12/2022-crop-cost-and-return-guide/[URL accessed Jan 2022]; Dobbins C, Langemeier MR, Nielsen B, Vyn TJ, Casteel S, and Johnson B (2020) Crop Production Costs Budget - Corn following Corn. Purdue University Cooperative Extension Service. https://ag.purdue.edu/commercialag/home/resource/2020/03/2020-crop-cost-and-return-guide/</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <normal meanValue="1.0166206218491E-05" variance="7.57894076947717E-13" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="7.57894076947717E-13"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="1" completeness="2" temporalCorrelation="2" geographicalCorrelation="1" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="1"/>
        </uncertainty>
