      <intermediateExchange id="6157857c-ee0b-52f1-9f08-ed71a6ae851f" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="4.58401625654488E-05" intermediateExchangeId="1be4f7e4-5244-4f9d-b80d-7fbf1e337e2b" activityLinkId="110a25f4-4a5e-5b5d-a1b3-818843c1f428">
        <name xml:lang="en">[thio]carbamate-compound</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">1.01E-2 MJ/kg diesel, burned in agricultural machinery 
Based on agricultural extension expert estimates of annual costs for haulage - moving grain from field to storage - and general fuel use (enterprise crop budgets including IA, NE, IL) and farmer survey data (Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (ISU), Wisconsin Farm Custom Rate Survey 2021 (USDA, NASS, Wisconsin Field Office)).
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance. Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. 
Sources:
ISU Extension 2021a; UNL Extension 2020; Langemeier MR, Nielsen B, Vyn TJ, Casteel S, and Johnson B 2021; Plastina, Johanns, Gleisner, Qualman 2021; WI NASS 2021
UNL Extension (2020) Nebraska Crop Budgets. Nebraska Extension, University of Nebraska–Lincoln Institute of Agriculture and Natural Resources. https://cropwatch.unl.edu/budgets, https://cropwatch.unl.edu/Budgets/2020/2020-NE-crop-budget-intro.pdf; Klein R and McClure G (2021a) 2021 Nebraska Crop Budgets EC872 - Dryland Corn. Nebraska Extension - Institute of Agriculture and Natural Resources, Universoty of Nebraska-Lincoln. https://cropwatch.unl.edu/Budgets/2021/2021-Corn-Dryland-121620.pdf; Klein R and McClure G (2021b) 2021 Nebraska Crop Budgets EC872 - Irrigated Corn. Nebraska Extension - Institute of Agriculture and Natural Resources, Universoty of Nebraska-Lincoln. https://cropwatch.unl.edu/Budgets/2021/2021-Corn-Irrigated-121620.pdf</comment>
