      <intermediateExchange id="f5da0ec6-c5fe-5c3c-905d-cdf7057688ce" unitId="86bbe475-8a8f-44d8-914c-e398787e7121" amount="2.80009384007224E-05" intermediateExchangeId="314f2225-6427-5e6b-9e51-9d07b203f102" activityLinkId="e453d20b-87b4-5ad9-8370-302ccb41426b">
        <name xml:lang="en">application of plant protection product, by airplane</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">0.3399 ha/ha (2.8E-5 ha/kg maize grain) application of plant protection product, by airplane
The dataset has an effective number of passes for application of pesticides of 1.44 ha: 1.09 applications of herbicides on 95.7% of cropped area, 1.05 applications of insecticides on 13.7% of cropped area, 1.07 applications of fungicides on 24.3% of cropped area (USDA NASS 2021f). Application by sprayer accounts for 76% (1.10 passes) and aircraft for 24% (0.34 passes). The budgets for maize grain in Iowa do not provide information for aerial pesticide application as an individual operation.  However, aerial application is in common use in Iowa. An aerial pesticide application rate of  24% has been estimated from custom rate surveys for contracted farm operations (Plastina A and Johanns A 2021; Plastina, Johanns, Massman 2020; Plastina, Johanns, Wynne 2019; Plastina, Johanns, Welter 2018).
Because aerial application is almost universally contracted service, it is most often not included in crop-specific enterprise budgets as a separate line item, instead being included under "custom" or "miscellaneous". Consequently, this dataset uses  the ratio of custom farm rate survey responses for aerial application to the total respondents to provide a state crop level average estimate of aerial applications.  This value covers all farmers responding and does not distinguish among crops. The Iowa Custom Rate Surveys, cited most widely in farm economics projections lacking the state's own Survey, average 24% 2018-2021 (Plastina A and Johanns A 2021, 2020, 2019, 2018).  The National Agricultural Aviation Association estimates that approximately 28% of all US cropland (excluding range, pasture, and forest lands) is treated by aircraft annually (NAAA 2019, NAAA 2020).
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance.  (ISU Extension 2021a, ISU Extension 2021b, ISU Extension 2021c, ISU Extension 2021d, ISU Extension 2021e, ISU Extension 2021f; Plastina A and Johanns A 2021, Hanna, Mark 2005).  Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. Where an operation applies only to a portion of the harvested area, the number of passes has been scaled by the % of harvested area to which it applies (e.g., manure spreading or insecticide) as indicated by USDA statistics (applications) or USDA reports (manure use) or as otherwise indicated in enterprise crop budgets.
Source(s): 
Plastina A and Johanns A (2021) Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (2018, 2019, 2020). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-10.pdf; Plastina, Johanns, Massman (2020) 2020 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://iastate.app.box.com/embed/s/hbsel0lckc7vle74v4jkg7mf0ph3z39s/file/630724245464; Plastina, Johanns, Wynne (2019) 2019 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/monroe/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/monroe/2019%20Custom%20Rate%20Survey.pdf; Plastina, Johanns, Welter (2018) 2018 Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey File A3-10. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/hancock/sites/www.extension.iastate.edu/files/hancock/2018_CustomRateSurvey.pdf; NAAA (2020) Letter to the South Dakota Public Utilities Commission, July 30, 2020. National Agricultural Aviation Association. https://puc.sd.gov/commission/dockets/electric/2021/EL21-018/prefiledexhibits/MBExhH.pdf; NAAA (2019) NAAA Member Survey Report. National Agricultural Aviation Association. https://www.agaviation.org/; USDA NASS (2021f) CORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG and NUMBER / YEAR (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/5BCE1263-5F91-31A9-B3DE-117AFBDDFF20); ISU Extension (2021a) Crop Production Costs Budgets - tabulated. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a1-20.pdf; ISU Extension (2021b) Crop Production Costs Budget - Corn following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfc_tbl1.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021c) Crop Production Costs Budget - Corn following Soybeans. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021d) Crop Production Costs Budget - Low-till corn following Soybeans. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20lowtillcfstbl6.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021e) Crop Production Costs Budget - Strip-till corn following Soybeans. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20striptillcfstbl5.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021f) Budgets and other resources from IA Extension. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/cdcostsreturns.html; Plastina A and Johanns A (2021) Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (2018, 2019, 2020). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-10.pdf; Hanna, Mark (2005) Fuel Required for Field Operations. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-24.pdf</comment>
