      <intermediateExchange id="243dc72f-3d02-565f-a5ec-39f146e67440" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" variableName="packaging_p" amount="0.000623331249292096" intermediateExchangeId="567c1e2d-b33a-4bf5-b4ad-d69926ce2f89" activityLinkId="f3da446d-c5d3-5187-bc6b-f07fc0f57771">
        <name xml:lang="en">packaging, for pesticides</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The total amount of active substance/s of pesticides used for the production of maize grain is calculated to be about 3.78 kg/ha (2014, 2016, 2018, 2021 - USDA NASS data, USDA NASS 2021f, USDA NASS 2021g). The total amount of active substance/s is doubled in order to account for the packaging of the diluted product of pesticides that are applied. Therefore, 7.57 kg of packaging for pesticides per ha maize grain (6.23E-4 kg/kg) is calculated with this exchange.</comment>
