      <intermediateExchange id="fd768715-ac27-5e45-bd4e-cfb7b380626c" unitId="86bbe475-8a8f-44d8-914c-e398787e7121" amount="6.17512432407979E-05" intermediateExchangeId="ee386cb2-7801-5f4b-a2c9-221bf2b75371" activityLinkId="78cd812c-3055-53fd-9299-31c84f8a1533">
        <name xml:lang="en">planting, by drill</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">6.18E-5 ha/kg planting (0.75 effective pass(es) per year). 
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance. Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. Field cultivation and tillage operations are specific to the tillage regime used.  The rotation pattern also dictates some tillage patterns, captured in the GIS data for tillage shares. Maize cultivation is 75% reduced till, 17% conventional tillage, and 8% no till in Iowa (CTIC 2020a). Sowing with till and no-till planters based on share of field type. Planting on reduced till fields only. 
Sources:
ISU Extension (2021a) Crop Production Costs Budgets - tabulated. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a1-20.pdf; ISU Extension (2021b) Crop Production Costs Budget - Corn following Corn. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfc_tbl1.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021c) Crop Production Costs Budget - Corn following Soybeans. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021d) Crop Production Costs Budget - Low-till corn following Soybeans. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20lowtillcfstbl6.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021e) Crop Production Costs Budget - Strip-till corn following Soybeans. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20striptillcfstbl5.xlsx; ISU Extension (2021f) Budgets and other resources from IA Extension. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/cdcostsreturns.html; Plastina A and Johanns A (2021) Iowa Farm Custom Rate Survey, 2021 (2018, 2019, 2020). Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-10.pdf; Hanna, Mark (2005) Fuel Required for Field Operations. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-24.pdf; CTIC (2020a) OpTIS - Operational Tillage Information System. Conservation Technology Information Center (CTIC). https://www.ctic.org/optis_tabular_queryaccessed March 23, 2021</comment>
