        <name xml:lang="en">Carbon dioxide, fossil</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">CO2 emissions from use of urea fertilisers and lime, 57.511 kg/ha (4.74E-3 kg/kg maize grain): 18.01 kg/ha from lime and 39.5 kg/ha from urea and urea ammonium nitrate. 
Emissions are calculated following the IPCC NIR Guidelines, §11.3 and §11.4, using IPCC NIR equations 11.12 (lime) and 11.13 (urea) (mass of lime/urea * emissions factor for lime/urea) with Tier 1 emissions factors (IPCC 2006b).  EF limestone = 0.12 kg CO2-C/kg limestone (0.06-0.12, uniform) and EF urea = 0.2 kg CO2-C/kg urea (0.1-0.2, uniform) applied to both urea and the approximately 35% of UAN that is urea. The result is converted from kg CO2-C to kg CO2 (multiplying by the molar mass of CO2/mass of C in CO2 = 44.01/12) 
Sources: IPCC (2006a) 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories - Chapter 11: N2O Emissions from Managed Soils, and CO2 Emissions from Lime and Urea Application in Volume 4: Agriculture, Forestry and Other Land Use. UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/pdf/4_Volume4/V4_11_Ch11_N2O&amp;CO2.pdf, https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/ 
