      <elementaryExchange id="aa438e51-462e-51e2-9e08-377d823fa8d0" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="014797-55-8" amount="0.00429291640953934" elementaryExchangeId="b9291c72-4b1d-4275-8068-4c707dc3ce33" formula="NO3-">
        <name xml:lang="en">Nitrate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The total nitrate leaching/runoff is 1.486E+2 kg NO3/ha (4.293E-3kg NO3/kg maize grain), 5.393E+1 kg NO3/ha from fertilisers, 4.136E+0 kg NO3/ha from manure, 9.460E+1 kg NO3/ha from soil mineralization, and -4.085E+0 kg NO3 N uptake. 
64.9% is emitted to surface water and 35.1% to ground water, since 64.9% of cropland in Iowa has drainage (USDA 2018).
Nitrate leaching is calculated with the SQCB-NO3 model (Faist Emmenegger et al. 2009) using general (state-level) parameters for slope and clay content, local precipitation and irrigation data. 
Sources: 
