      <elementaryExchange id="0f34bad3-3ec7-559a-9e5f-6c7f07bc4162" unitId="eb955b7c-7bed-401f-9c76-5db716ca3640" amount="0.00329816742213787" elementaryExchangeId="c4a82f46-381f-474c-a362-3363064b9c33">
        <name xml:lang="en">Occupation, annual crop, irrigated</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m2*year</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Land occupation per year (annual growing season).  Land is under rotation with other annual crop production (~80% corn-soy, ~20% corn-corn, Socolar et al 2021).  US NRCS data indicates that total cropland in Iowa has expanded 3% over the last 20 years, met entirely by land idled under the Conservation Reserve Program (CRP) (NRCS 2020b), resulting in a flux to/from annual crop that is essentially steady state. 
Annual production is 63.6 million tonnes from 2014-2021 on 5.4 million ha planted and 5.3 million ha harvested (USDA NASS 2021d). Thus occupation is 0.82 ha/t or 8,238.81 m2/t (0.8239 m2/kg). This overall land use is split into irrigated (0.4%) and non-irrigated (99.6%) based on agricultural census data (USDA NASS 2021d) (3.3E-3 m2 planted/kg harvested maize of irrigated land, and 8.21E-1 m2 planted/kg harvested maize of non-irrigated land).
Sources:
USDA NASS (2021d) Area, Production, Yield by State - Corn - 2010-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov (direct query: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/results/331F88CC-004E-34D2-B825-F8F65DAC7879)
NRCS (2020b)  Land Cover/use of non-Federal rural land, by State and year, in the 2017 National Resources Inventory. USDA, Natural Resources Conservation Service. http://www.nrcs.usda.gov/Internet/NRCS_RCA/reports/nri_crop_nat.html, https://www.nrcs.usda.gov/wps/portal/nrcs/rca/national/technical/nra/rca/text/#NRI%20Cropland
Socolar Y, Goldstein B R, de Valpine P, Bowles T M (2021) Biophysical and policy factors predict simplified crop rotations in the US Midwest.  Environ. Res. Lett. 16 054045. . https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/1748-9326/abf9ca</comment>
